 Recurring pneumothorax associated with menstruation was first described in 1958. In spite of the rare appearance of catamenial pneumothorax, there is no reason for underemphasized treatment. There is no universally accepted explanation for the pathogenesis of the pneumothorax. We believe that the extragenital endometriosis of the lung or diaphragm is the cause of pneumothorax. By pneumothorax, affected women often undergo several episodes before correct diagnosis is possible.  
